{
  "stem": "490.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It-- you-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was always, you know, no matter how strong you are, you asked yourself where is, where is anything that you were so convinced all your life, anything that you are, you will-- you think it's always somebody is interested in, if it's a high power or whatever, there's-- and we saw the, the, the atrocities and the way people were just-- you know, the best of people, the best in the world, the best what, what what life could put together, they were just slaughtered-- young children.",
      "word_count": 94
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had a teacher which, he had a child, a baby, after so many years of not having children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when the Germans came, and when they, they, they came, they had to send away all the people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they wanted-- they took him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they wanted to take away his baby, and he fight, he fought.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He didn't let them take his only little-- maybe a year old or so.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in front of his eyes, they took the baby.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they threw it, and they smashed his head against the wall.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave it to him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They said, here, you want your child?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Here it is.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when you see those things, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sometimes you know, you lose your courage, your lose your, your strength, what keeps you, kept you.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it's very difficult to continue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it's not that the suffering that you had not having enough, not to have freedom, or not to have enough food.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It is just inside that, that they--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What they say about Amalek, Amalek, they say don't forget.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The system of Amalek, it's not-- they say they want to break your spirit inside, the same as-- not long ago we had Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
